The paper focuses on human-robot collaboration, which is a core topic in robotics (cs.RO). The proposed framework involves plan recognition and trajectory prediction, which are both key components of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also emphasizes the importance of safety and efficiency in human-robot collaboration, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The framework involves machine learning techniques, which are often used in large-scale data analysis and pattern recognition (cs.LG). Finally, the paper mentions the use of computer vision techniques to perceive the human's actions, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV).
